  "2026-07-10T17:51:58.069Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: active in the broad atomic work-selection and agent recovery PR. Live all-status duplicate check, full item metadata, closed prerequisite lineage, GitHub issues, security alerts, dependency audit, release state, and Sentry issue surface were reviewed before claiming. This item shares CLI/SDK contracts, recovery envelopes, and end-to-end verification with the seven sibling items in the bundle."
  "2026-07-10T17:52:50.422Z",codex-root,"Live verification correction: current main 0f43e921 already resolves cwd-rooted tracker layouts. Fresh temp proof: pm init . --defaults --author probe created tracker-path mode at cwd; the immediately following bare pm list --json exited 0 and returned an empty item list. Root cause was already removed by the root-layout discovery work linked through pm-x26a/GH-495; no code change belongs in this PR."
close_reason: Already fixed on current main; fresh init-then-list temp proof exits 0 with implicit root-layout discovery.
body: "## Problem\npm init <path> (tracker-path mode) roots the tracker at the path directly, but workspace discovery for every subsequent command only probes <cwd>/.agents/pm. The very next command fails with tracker_not_initialized telling the agent to run pm init first — a hard loop: the error's next_steps re-suggest the action that caused the state. pm init . is the natural git/npm-muscle-memory spelling for 'init here', the failure is delayed (init reports ok:true), and the recovery bundle mentions neither the cwd-rooted tracker nor --pm-path. Worst case the agent re-inits and silently splits state across two trackers.\n\n## Repro (pm 2026.7.10)\nmkdir ws && cd ws && pm init . -> ok, mode tracker-path, tracker_root=<cwd>. pm list --json -> tracker_not_initialized at <cwd>/.agents/pm. pm --pm-path . list --json works.\n\n## Fix directions (from GH-501, any-of)\n1. Discovery also accepts cwd (or ancestor) as tracker root when it contains a valid settings.json + tracker layout.\n2. Treat pm init . as the workspace-discovery spelling (.agents/pm under it); require an explicit --tracker-path for raw-root mode.\n3. Minimum: tracker_not_initialized probes cwd for a tracker and suggests --pm-path . as an executable next step.\nOption 1+3 together preserve both modes without breaking existing raw-root users; option 2 is a behavior change needing a deprecation note. Related: pm-x26a (GH-488) made path-target init emit tracker-scoped follow-up commands — same mode-split root cause, this is the discovery half.\n\n## Philosophy tie-in\nNever-block: an error whose recovery loop re-suggests its own cause is the worst agent dead-end.\n\n## Source\nhttps://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/501"
